Looking at classes.berkeley.edu (which is delayed), I don't see the lecture as being listed as full.

If that were the case, it might mean that the enrollment is capped by the total class capacity, but they want to allow students a bit more leeway in choosing which section to enroll for. This is rare, but happens occasionally.

But also, see @2911.

Hello! I'd really like to enroll for Data 8 next semester and I noticed that there were still open lab spots, but the lecture had reached capacity.

I'm not really sure what that means and was wondering whether there was a possibility the lecture class size might be expanded? I'd really love to sign up for this class when Phase 3 opens.

Thanks!
